  "body": "Trying the revamped Remix, using geth as a backend. When setting `Environment: Web3 provider` and trying the local rpc node, the following happens: \r\n\r\nRemix (via firefox) does an `OPTIONS`:\r\n```\r\nOPTIONS / HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: localhost:8546\r\nUser-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Fedora; Linux x86_64; rv:68.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/68.0\r\nAccept: */*\r\nAccept-Language: en-US,en;q=0.5\r\nAccept-Encoding: gzip, deflate\r\nAccess-Control-Request-Method: POST\r\nAccess-Control-Request-Headers: content-type\r\nReferer: http://remix.ethereum.org/\r\nOrigin: http://remix.ethereum.org\r\nDNT: 1\r\nConnection: close\r\n\r\n```\r\nTo which geth answers\r\n```\r\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nContent-Type: application/json\r\nDate: Fri, 20 Sep 2019 07:36:22 GMT\r\nContent-Length: 0\r\nConnection: close\r\n\r\n```",
